{
  "_comment": [
    "Per-category / per-source MEMORY BUDGET baseline for the CI memory gate.",
    "These are CEILINGS, not targets: shrink them, don't grow them. The gate",
    "(Tools/check_memory_budget.py) fails when (a) a budgeted entry's budget is",
    "raised without justification, (b) a budget drops below its own recorded",
    "baseline_peak, or (c) a live-captured actual peak exceeds budget or regresses",
    "beyond tolerance_pct vs baseline_peak_bytes.",
    "",
    "ci_capturable=true entries are measurable on the default headless GitHub runner",
    "(CPU categories + Jolt via a bounded --memory-dump boot). ci_capturable=false",
    "entries (RENDERER / VMA VRAM) need a GPU and are only enforced on the self-hosted",
    "GPU runner. baseline_peak_bytes=0 means 'not yet measured' (ratchet-only).",
    "",
    "Regenerate captured peaks with:  python Tools/check_memory_budget.py --update <csv>"
  ],
